SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 416
By Lamar
A RESOLUTION to recognize and commend the University of
Memphis Athletic Department.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly take great pleasure in recognizing
the University of Memphis (UM) Athletic Department, whose teams compete at the highest level
of athletic competition as a National Collegiate Athletic Association Division I institution and a
charter member of the American Athletic Conference (AAC); and
WHEREAS, UM Athletics currently has nineteen intercollegiate sports teams, and since
joining the conference in 2013, has won thirteen AAC titles across all sports; and
WHEREAS, the 2024 Memphis Tigers football team, led by Coach Ryan Silverfield, won
its fifth consecutive bowl game and recorded back-to-back ten-win seasons for the first time in
program history; and
WHEREAS, the Memphis Tigers football team finished the season ranked No. 23 in the
Coaches Poll and No. 24 in the AP Poll, marking the first time since 2019 that the Tigers ranked
in either poll at season's end; and
WHEREAS, furthermore, the Tigers football team currently holds the longest active
streak in the nation for scoring twenty or more points in forty consecutive games; and
WHEREAS, Memphis football either ranked or received votes in the AP Poll for ten
weeks and the Coaches Poll for fourteen weeks during the 2024 season; and
WHEREAS, with eleven wins, Memphis football posted its first back-to-back double-digit-
win seasons in program history and was 21-5 overall for the past two seasons, the most wins
garnered in two years in Memphis's history; and
