WHEREAS, the perseverance, determination, work ethic, and talent of the University of
Memphis Athletic Department have not only made possible championship seasons but also
surely bode well for future successes; and
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly find it appropriate to acknowledge
and applaud the students, coaches, and staff of the University of Memphis Athletic Department;
now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we recognize and commend the students, coaches,
and staff of the University of Memphis Athletic Department and extend to them our best wishes
for future success and happiness.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
